></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ecg1720075856889.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecg1720075856889.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecg1720075856889.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gst1665703005142\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gst1665703005142__javascript_224523\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Declares a JavaScript block in a client-side trigger or operation.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gst1665703005142__topic_d73604e1_d73605e1_d73606e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73607e1_d73608e1_d73609e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">javascript</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73610e1_d73611e1_d73612e1\">...<var class=\"keyword varname\">Your JavaScript code here</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73613e1_d73614e1_d73615e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">endjavascript</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gst1665703005142__topic_d48407e1_d48408e1_d48409e1_d48410e1_d48411e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d340768e77\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__d5966e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gst1665703005142__topic_d48412e1_d48413e1_d48414e1_d48415e1_d48416e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d340768e86\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73625e1_d73626e1_d73627e1\">Use in Dynamic Server Page components.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73628e1_d73629e1_d73630e1\">Only for use in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">weboperation</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webtrigger</span> definitions.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gst1665703005142__topic_d48417e1_d48418e1_d48419e1_d48420e1_d48421e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d340768e104\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73634e1_d73635e1_d73636e1\">Use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">javascript</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">endjavascript</span> instructions to define a block of JavaScript code\n            that contains one or more JavaScript functions. In this code, you can make use of the\n            Uniface JavaScript API to address and manipulate data, occurrences, and component\n            instances. The JavaScript must conform to the data format described in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sah1665702594971.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sah1665702594971.html\" title=\"You can use your preferred JavaScript editor to maintain your JavaScript implementation externally, for example in an external DSP layout or JavaScript files. This enables you to take advantage of JavaScript validation and debugging functionality that is not provided by Uniface. To do so, you need to implement client-side triggers and operations as JavaScript functions and add them as members of a JavaScript object tree.\">Data Format of External Client-Side Triggers and Operations</a>. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73637e1_d73638e1_d73639e1\">Uniface treats anything between the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">javascript</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">endjavascript</span> instructions as JavaScript, but does not validate it. However, if your JavaScript contains either of these keywords on a separate line, Uniface interprets them as ProcScript instructions and this can result in syntax errors.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gst1665703005142__note_w1633ab1b7b9b7_w1634ab1b7b9_w1635ab1b7_w1636ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Code highlighting is currently not available for JavaScript in the ProcScript Editor. ProcScript keywords and syntax are highlighted wherever they occur, so Javascript code that matches a ProcScript keyword is highlighted, even though it is not ProcScript. This has no effect on compilation.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73640e1_d73641e1_d73642e1\">Parameters for client-side operations and triggers are optional and must be declared in ProcScript preceding the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">javascript</span> instruction. Variables, however, must be declared in JavaScript.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gst1665703005142__p_d73643e1_d73644e1_d73645e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vkk1665702595354.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkk1665702595354.html\" title=\"Client-side triggers and operations are run in the browser on the client and are implemented in JavaScript. They can be used only in dynamic server pages.\">Client-Side Triggers and Operations</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">weboperation AlertJS \nscope \n input\n output\nendscope\njavascript ; ProcScript instruction, so ProcScript comment can follow\n alert(\"THIS IS JAVASCRIPT CODING\"); /* JavaScript code, so comment is also JavaScript*/\nendjavascript ; ProcScript instruction, so ProcScript comment can follow\nend ;alert operation</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lem1707814690530.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>JavaScript</a><p>JavaScript is a widely-used scripting language used to extend HTML with dynamic behavior. Uniface supports the use of JavaScript to implement script modules in Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs), and provides an API for addressing Uniface data objects.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a><p>The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dnz1665702532513.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Executing Logic in the Browser</a><p>Uniface provides extensive support for executing logic in the browser, making it possible to reduce unnecessary data exchange between the client and the server.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7431127\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7431127\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "javascript Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Declares a JavaScript block in a client-side trigger or operation. javascript ... Your JavaScript code here endjavascript Return Values None Use Use in Dynamic Server Page components. Only for use in weboperation and webtrigger definitions. Description Use javascript and endjavascript instructions to define a block of JavaScript code that contains one or more JavaScript functions. In this code, you can make use of the Uniface JavaScript API to address and manipulate data, occurrences, and component instances. The JavaScript must conform to the data format described in Data Format of External Client-Side Triggers and Operations . Uniface treats anything between the javascript and endjavascript instructions as JavaScript, but does not validate it. However, if your JavaScript contains either of these keywords on a separate line, Uniface interprets them as ProcScript instructions and this can result in syntax errors. Note: Code highlighting is currently not available for JavaScript in the ProcScript Editor. ProcScript keywords and syntax are highlighted wherever they occur, so Javascript code that matches a ProcScript keyword is highlighted, even though it is not ProcScript. This has no effect on compilation. Parameters for client-side operations and triggers are optional and must be declared in ProcScript preceding the javascript instruction. Variables, however, must be declared in JavaScript. For more information, see Client-Side Triggers and Operations . weboperation AlertJS scope input output endscope javascript ; ProcScript instruction, so ProcScript comment can follow alert(\"THIS IS JAVASCRIPT CODING\"); /* JavaScript code, so comment is also JavaScript*/ endjavascript ; ProcScript instruction, so ProcScript comment can follow end ;alert operation Copy Related Links JavaScript JavaScript is a widely-used scripting language used to extend HTML with dynamic behavior. Uniface supports the use of JavaScript to implement script modules in Dynamic Server Pages (DSPs), and provides an API for addressing Uniface data objects. APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server. Executing Logic in the Browser Uniface provides extensive support for executing logic in the browser, making it possible to reduce unnecessary data exchange between the client and the server. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}